36static OSStatus createWebKitVP8Decoder(FigVideoCodecType, CFAllocatorRef allocator, VTVideoDecoderRef*);
37void registerWebKitVP8Decoder()
38{
39 VTRegisterVideoDecoder('vp08', createWebKitVP8Decoder);
40}
41
42typedef struct {
43 std::unique_ptr<LibvpxVp8Decoder> m_instance;
44 std::unique_ptr<WebKitDecoderReceiver> m_receiver;
45} WebKitVP8Decoder;
46
47static OSStatus invalidateVP8Decoder(CMBaseObjectRef);
48static void finalizeVP8Decoder(CMBaseObjectRef);
49static CFStringRef copyVP8DecoderDebugDescription(CMBaseObjectRef);
50
51#if defined(CMBASE_OBJECT_NEEDS_ALIGNMENT) && CMBASE_OBJECT_NEEDS_ALIGNMENT
52 constexpr size_t padSize = 4;
53#else
54 constexpr size_t padSize = 0;
55#endif
56
57#pragma pack(push, 4)
58struct DecoderClass {
59 uint8_t pad[padSize];
60 CMBaseClass alignedClass;
61};
62
63static const DecoderClass WebKitVP8Decoder_BaseClass {
64 { },
65 {
66 kCMBaseObject_ClassVersion_1,
67 sizeof(WebKitVP8Decoder),
68 nullptr, // Comparison by pointer equality
69 invalidateVP8Decoder,
70 finalizeVP8Decoder,
71 copyVP8DecoderDebugDescription,
72 nullptr, // CopyProperty
73 nullptr, // SetProperty
74 nullptr,
75 nullptr
76 }
77};
78#pragma pack(pop)
79
80#if defined(CMBASE_OBJECT_NEEDS_ALIGNMENT) && CMBASE_OBJECT_NEEDS_ALIGNMENT
81 static_assert(sizeof(WebKitVP8Decoder_BaseClass.alignedClass.version) == sizeof(uint32_t), "CMBaseClass fixup is required!");
82#else
83 static_assert(sizeof(WebKitVP8Decoder_BaseClass.alignedClass.version) == sizeof(uintptr_t), "CMBaseClass fixup is not required!");
84#endif
85static_assert(offsetof(DecoderClass, alignedClass) == padSize, "CMBaseClass offset is incorrect!");
86static_assert(alignof(DecoderClass) == 4, "CMBaseClass must have 4 byte alignment");
87
88static OSStatus startVP8DecoderSession(VTVideoDecoderRef, VTVideoDecoderSession, CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef);
89static OSStatus decodeVP8DecoderFrame(VTVideoDecoderRef, VTVideoDecoderFrame, CMSampleBufferRef, VTDecodeFrameFlags, VTDecodeInfoFlags*);

91static const VTVideoDecoderClass WebKitVP8Decoder_VideoDecoderClass =
92{
93 kVTVideoDecoder_ClassVersion_1,
94 startVP8DecoderSession,
95 decodeVP8DecoderFrame,
96 nullptr, // VTVideoDecoderFunction_CopySupportedPropertyDictionary,
97 nullptr, // VTVideoDecoderFunction_SetProperties
98 nullptr, // VTVideoDecoderFunction_CopySerializableProperties
99 nullptr, // VTVideoDecoderFunction_CanAcceptFormatDescription
100 nullptr, // VTVideoDecoderFunction_FinishDelayedFrames
101 nullptr, // VTVideoDecoderFunction_StartTileSession
102 nullptr, // VTVideoDecoderFunction_DecodeTile
103 nullptr // VTVideoDecoderFunction_FinishDelayedTiles
104};

106static const VTVideoDecoderVTable WebKitVP8DecoderVTable =
107{
108 { nullptr, &WebKitVP8Decoder_BaseClass.alignedClass },
109 &WebKitVP8Decoder_VideoDecoderClass
110};
111
112OSStatus createWebKitVP8Decoder(FigVideoCodecType, CFAllocatorRef allocator, VTVideoDecoderRef* decoderOut)
113{
114 if (!decoderOut) {
115 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP8 decoder creation failed, no decoder output";
116 return kVTParameterErr;
117 }
118
119 VTVideoDecoderRef decoder = nullptr;
120 auto error = CMDerivedObjectCreate(allocator, &WebKitVP8DecoderVTable.base, VTVideoDecoderGetClassID(), (CMBaseObjectRef*)&decoder);
121
122 if (!decoder) {
123 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP8 decoder creation failed, CMDerivedObjectCreate failed with error " << error;
124 return kVTAllocationFailedErr;
125 }
126
127 if(error) {
128 CFRelease(decoder);
129 decoder = NULL;
130 }
131 *decoderOut = decoder;
132 return error;
133}
134
135OSStatus invalidateVP8Decoder(CMBaseObjectRef instance)
136{
137 auto* decoder = static_cast<WebKitVP8Decoder*>(CMBaseObjectGetDerivedStorage(instance));
138 if (!decoder)
139 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP8 decoder: invalidation failed as instance has no decoder";
140 else {
141 decoder->m_instance = nullptr;
142 decoder->m_receiver = nullptr;
143 }
144 return noErr;
145}
146
147void finalizeVP8Decoder(CMBaseObjectRef instance)
148{
149 invalidateVP8Decoder(instance);
150}
151
152CFStringRef copyVP8DecoderDebugDescription(CMBaseObjectRef)
153{
154 return CFSTR("WebKit VP8 decoder");
155}
156
157WebKitVP8Decoder* webKitVP8DecoderFromVTDecoder(VTVideoDecoderRef decoder)
158{
159 return static_cast<WebKitVP8Decoder*>(CMBaseObjectGetDerivedStorage(reinterpret_cast<CMBaseObjectRef>(decoder)));
160}
161OSStatus startVP8DecoderSession(VTVideoDecoderRef instance, VTVideoDecoderSession session, CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef formatDescription)
162{
163 auto* decoder = webKitVP8DecoderFromVTDecoder(instance);
164 if (!decoder) {
165 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP8 decoder: failed to get decoder from instance while starting";
166 return kVTParameterErr;
167 }
168
169 decoder->m_instance = std::make_unique<LibvpxVp8Decoder>();
170 decoder->m_receiver = std::make_unique<WebKitDecoderReceiver>(session);
171 decoder->m_receiver->initializeFromFormatDescription(formatDescription);
172
173 decoder->m_instance->RegisterDecodeCompleteCallback(decoder->m_receiver.get());
174
175 VideoCodec codec;
176 auto dimensions = CMVideoFormatDescriptionGetDimensions(formatDescription);
177 codec.width = dimensions.width;
178 codec.height = dimensions.height;
179
180 decoder->m_instance->InitDecode(&codec, CpuInfo::DetectNumberOfCores());
181
182 return noErr;
183}
184
185static OSStatus decodeVP8DecoderFrameFromContiguousBlock(WebKitVP8Decoder& decoder, VTVideoDecoderFrame frame, CMBlockBufferRef encodedBuffer)
186{
187 RTC_DCHECK(CMBlockBufferIsRangeContiguous(encodedBuffer, 0, 0));
188
189 auto size = CMBlockBufferGetDataLength(encodedBuffer);
190 char* data = nullptr;
191 if (auto error = CMBlockBufferGetDataPointer(encodedBuffer, 0, nullptr, nullptr, &data)) {
192 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP8 decoder: CMBlockBufferGetDataPointer failed with error " << error;
193 return error;
194 }
195
196 RTC_DCHECK(!decoder.m_receiver->currentFrame());
197 decoder.m_receiver->setCurrentFrame(frame);
198
199 EncodedImage image;
200 image.SetEncodedData(WebKitEncodedImageBufferWrapper::create(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(data), size));
201 // We set those values as VP8DecoderImpl checks for getting a full key frame as first frame.
202 image._frameType = VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
203 auto error = decoder.m_instance->Decode(image, false, 0);
204 if (error)
205 return decoder.m_receiver->decoderFailed(error);
206
207 RTC_DCHECK(!decoder.m_receiver->currentFrame());
208
209 return 0;
210}
211
212OSStatus decodeVP8DecoderFrame(VTVideoDecoderRef instance, VTVideoDecoderFrame frame, CMSampleBufferRef sampleBuffer, VTDecodeFrameFlags, VTDecodeInfoFlags*)
213{
214 auto* decoder = webKitVP8DecoderFromVTDecoder(instance);
215 if (!decoder || !decoder->m_instance || !decoder->m_receiver) {
216 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP8 decoder: failed to get decoder from instance while decoding";
217 return kVTParameterErr;
218 }
219
220 auto encodedBuffer = CMSampleBufferGetDataBuffer(sampleBuffer);
221 if (!encodedBuffer) {
222 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP8 decoder: failed to get data buffer";
223 return kVTParameterErr;
224 }
225
226 CMBlockBufferRef contiguousBuffer = nullptr;
227 // Make sure block buffer is contiguous.
228 if (!CMBlockBufferIsRangeContiguous(encodedBuffer, 0, 0)) {
229 auto status = CMBlockBufferCreateContiguous(nullptr, encodedBuffer, nullptr, nullptr, 0, 0, 0, &contiguousBuffer);
230 if (status != noErr) {
231 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP8 decoder: failed to create contiguous block buffer with error " << status;
232 return kVTAllocationFailedErr;
233 }
234 encodedBuffer = contiguousBuffer;
235 }
236
237 auto result = decodeVP8DecoderFrameFromContiguousBlock(*decoder, frame, encodedBuffer);
238
239 if (contiguousBuffer)
240 CFRelease(contiguousBuffer);
241
242 return result;
243}
